title: Williams throws for 4 TDs to lead Dartmouth past Yale, 35-3
text:
Dalyn Williams passes for 435 yards, 4 TDs to help Dartmouth stay undefeated, beat Yale 35-3 THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   6:15   6:15   
Subjects: 
New Hampshire (310) 

HANOVER, New Hampshire — Dalyn Williams passed for a career-high 435 yards and four touchdowns to help Dartmouth remain undefeated and beat Yale 35-3 on Saturday. 
Williams became Dartmouth's career leader in total offense (7,525), passing former NFL quarterback Jay Fiedler (1991-93). Williams moved past Brian Mann into second on the school's all-time passing list with 6,080 yards, trailing only Fiedler (6,684). 
Ryan McManus, who sat out the last two games with an ankle sprain, and Jon Marc Carrier had six receptions apiece. McManus finished with 116 yards receiving and Carrier added 103. Cameron Skaff had two touchdown catches for the Big Green (4-0, 2-0 Ivy League). 
Dartmouth took 21-0 lead when Williams hit Kyle Bramble for a 17-yard touchdown with 6:28 left in the first half. 
Yale (3-1, 1-1), which came into the game averaging more than 457 yards and nearly 30 points per game, was limited to a season-low 276 total yards.
